# API Endpoints Guide

## API Structure Pattern

Each endpoint file in [app/api/api_v1/endpoints/](mdc:app/api/api_v1/endpoints/) follows this pattern:

```python
from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException
from sqlalchemy.orm import Session
from app.core.database import get_db
from app.schemas import [SchemaName]
from app.services import [ServiceName]
from app.core.auth import get_current_user

router = APIRouter()

@router.get("/endpoint")
async def get_something(
    db: Session = Depends(get_db),
    current_user = Depends(get_current_user)
):
    return await service.get_something(db, current_user)
```

## Available Endpoints

### Authentication Endpoints
- `POST /auth/login` - User login
- `POST /auth/register` - User registration
- `GET /auth/me` - Get current user info

### User Management
- `GET /users/profile` - Get user profile
- `PUT /users/profile` - Update user profile
- `GET /users/{user_id}` - Get specific user

### Property Management
- `GET /properties/` - List properties with filtering
- `GET /properties/{property_id}` - Get specific property
- `POST /properties/` - Create property (agents only)
- `PUT /properties/{property_id}` - Update property (agents only)
- `DELETE /properties/{property_id}` - Delete property (agents only)

### Agent Management
- `GET /agents/` - List agents
- `GET /agents/{agent_id}` - Get specific agent
- `POST /agents/` - Create agent profile
- `PUT /agents/{agent_id}` - Update agent profile

### Booking System
- `GET /bookings/` - List user bookings
- `GET /bookings/{booking_id}` - Get specific booking
- `POST /bookings/` - Create booking
- `PUT /bookings/{booking_id}` - Update booking
- `DELETE /bookings/{booking_id}` - Cancel booking

### Visit Scheduling
- `GET /visits/` - List scheduled visits
- `GET /visits/{visit_id}` - Get specific visit
- `POST /visits/` - Schedule visit
- `PUT /visits/{visit_id}` - Update visit
- `DELETE /visits/{visit_id}` - Cancel visit

### Swipe Interactions
- `GET /swipes/` - List user swipes
- `POST /swipes/` - Record swipe action
- `GET /swipes/matches` - Get matched properties

## Error Handling

Common HTTP status codes:
- `200` - Success
- `201` - Created
- `400` - Bad Request
- `401` - Unauthorized
- `403` - Forbidden
- `404` - Not Found
- `422` - Validation Error
- `500` - Internal Server Error

## Authentication Requirements

- **Public endpoints**: No authentication required
- **Protected endpoints**: `Depends(get_current_user)` required
- **Agent-only endpoints**: `Depends(get_current_user)` + role check required